# Feature: simulation continuation (save/restore state)
# Tests: two-phase simulation with state save/load at midpoint
# Covers: --save-state, --load-state, --t-start flags
# Tier: base
# Expected: Phase 1 equilibrates binding; Phase 2 continues from saved state.
#           Observable values at the join point must match exactly.
#           Trajectories are statistically equivalent to a single-phase run.
# Note: NFsim does NOT support continue=>1; this is RM-only functionality.
#
# Validation: run Phase 1 (0-50), save state, load state, run Phase 2 (50-100).
# Compare Phase 2 start values against Phase 1 end values (must be identical).
# Compare overall trajectory statistics against ODE or single-phase RM.

begin model
begin parameters
    A_tot   100
    B_tot   100
    kf      0.01    # /s, binding rate
    kr      0.5     # /s, unbinding rate
end parameters

begin molecule types
    A(b)
    B(a)
end molecule types

begin seed species
    A(b)  A_tot
    B(a)  B_tot
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  Afree   A(b)
    Molecules  Bfree   B(a)
    Molecules  AB      A(b!1).B(a!1)
end observables

begin reaction rules
    A(b) + B(a) <-> A(b!1).B(a!1)  kf, kr
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>100,n_steps=>100})
end actions
